        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 6:22PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 622 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles south of Paoli, or 10 miles southwest of Holyoke, moving north
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree branches and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Holyoke, Paoli, Fairfield and Highland Center.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
